#MEM id=rules source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/dev/skills/design-and-build/vercel-composition-patterns/rules/architecture-avoid-boolean-props.md
M|rules|title: Avoid Boolean Prop Proliferation
M|rules|impact: CRITICAL
M|rules|impactDescription: prevents unmaintainable component variants
M|rules|tags: composition, props, architecture
M|rules|Don't add boolean props like `isThread`, `isEditing`, `isDMThread` to customize
M|rules|component behavior. Each boolean doubles possible states and creates
M|rules|unmaintainable conditional logic. Use composition instead.
M|rules|**Incorrect (boolean props create exponential complexity):**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|function Composer({
M|rules|onSubmit,
M|rules|isThread,
M|rules|channelId,
M|rules|isDMThread,
M|rules|dmId,
M|rules|isEditing,
M|rules|isForwarding,
M|rules|}: Props) {
M|rules|return (
M|rules|<form>
M|rules|<Header />
M|rules|<Input />
M|rules|{isDMThread ? (
M|rules|<AlsoSendToDMField id={dmId} />
M|rules|) : isThread ? (
M|rules|<AlsoSendToChannelField id={channelId} />
M|rules|) : null}
M|rules|{isEditing ? (
M|rules|<EditActions />
M|rules|) : isForwarding ? (
M|rules|<ForwardActions />
M|rules|) : (
M|rules|<DefaultActions />
M|rules|)}
M|rules|<Footer onSubmit={onSubmit} />
M|rules|</form>
M|rules|)
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|**Correct (composition eliminates conditionals):**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|// Channel composer
M|rules|function ChannelComposer() {
M|rules|return (
M|rules|<Composer.Frame>
M|rules|<Composer.Header />
M|rules|<Composer.Input />
M|rules|<Composer.Footer>
M|rules|<Composer.Attachments />
M|rules|<Composer.Formatting />
M|rules|<Composer.Emojis />
M|rules|<Composer.Submit />
M|rules|</Composer.Footer>
M|rules|</Composer.Frame>
M|rules|)
M|rules|}
M|rules|// Thread composer - adds "also send to channel" field
M|rules|function ThreadComposer({ channelId }: { channelId: string }) {
M|rules|return (
M|rules|<Composer.Frame>
M|rules|<Composer.Header />
M|rules|<Composer.Input />
M|rules|<AlsoSendToChannelField id={channelId} />
M|rules|<Composer.Footer>
M|rules|<Composer.Formatting />
M|rules|<Composer.Emojis />
M|rules|<Composer.Submit />
M|rules|</Composer.Footer>
M|rules|</Composer.Frame>
M|rules|)
M|rules|}
M|rules|// Edit composer - different footer actions
M|rules|function EditComposer() {
M|rules|return (
M|rules|<Composer.Frame>
M|rules|<Composer.Input />
M|rules|<Composer.Footer>
M|rules|<Composer.Formatting />
M|rules|<Composer.Emojis />
M|rules|<Composer.CancelEdit />
M|rules|<Composer.SaveEdit />
M|rules|</Composer.Footer>
M|rules|</Composer.Frame>
M|rules|)
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|Each variant is explicit about what it renders. We can share internals without
M|rules|sharing a single monolithic parent.